The '''Ted Hendricks Award''' is given annually to [[college football]]'s top [[defensive end]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Alex|last=Makrides|title=Two FSU defensive ends named to Ted Hendricks Award watch list|date=August 22, 2017|newspaper=The Palm Beach Post|url=https://www.palmbeachpost.com/story/sports/2017/08/22/two-fsu-defensive-ends-named/7247919007/|access-date=December 8, 2023}}</ref> The award is named after [[Ted Hendricks]], a member of both the [[College Football Hall of Fame]] and [[Pro Football Hall of Fame]], and is presented by his own foundation. In 2022, [[Caleb Murphy]], of [[NCAA Division II]] [[Ferris State Bulldogs football|Ferris State University]], became the first non-FBS player to win the award.<ref name=ferris>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-21 |title=Ferris State's Caleb Murphy Becomes First-Ever Non-FBS Player To Win Prestigious Ted Hendricks Award |url=https://www.ferrisstatebulldogs.com/sports/fball/2022-23/releases/20221221km774i |publisher=Ferris State Bulldogs|language=en}}</ref> The most recent recipient of the award was [[Rueben Bain Jr.]] from [[Miami Hurricanes football|Miami (FL)]].

